com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.packet.pool

Interface Pool<T>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FluidPool<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteBufferReceivablePacketPool, QueuedPool

    public Pool<T>

    A supplier of objects that reuses passed old ones. This allows for less instances and thus more efficiency.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  Pool.DefaultImpls
      A supplier of objects that reuses passed old ones. This allows for less instances and thus more efficiency.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T clear(T item)
      Makes the passed item available for reuse, and thus able to be passed to the pool.
      boolean clearAndRelease(T item)
      Calls clear on the passed item and THEN releases it.
      T get() 
      T getNextItem()
      returns the next item in the pool. Equivalent to calling Pool.get.
      boolean release(T item)
      Releases the passed item back into the pool WITHOUT clearing it first.
